# Markdown Conventions

## File Naming

- No spaces in filenames — use hyphens: `sif-v3.md`, `s5la-v1.md`
- Include version in name when document has versioned history
- `foundation/` — S5LA base layer documents
- `framework/` — SIF/SSF security framework documents

## Required Lint Compliance

All `.md` files must pass markdownlint with zero errors:

- **MD022** — blank line above and below every heading
- **MD031** — blank line before and after every fenced code block
- **MD032** — blank line before and after every list
- **MD036** — never use `**bold**` as a heading substitute; use `####` instead
- **MD040** — every fenced code block must have a language tag (`text`, `markdown`, `bash`, etc.)
- **MD060** — table separator rows must use `| --- |` format (not `|---|`)

## Table Format

```markdown
| Column A | Column B |
| --- | --- |
| value | value |
```

Never use `|---|` — always `| --- |`.

## Code Block Language Tags

| Content type | Language tag |
| --- | --- |
| ASCII diagram / checklist | `text` |
| Prompt template / system prompt | `markdown` |
| Shell commands | `bash` |
| Prose code blocks | `text` |

## Document Update Protocol

When updating any framework document:

1. Check canonical priority — only edit the highest-authority document for the topic
2. Do not modify `foundation/s5la-v1.md` definitions (frozen)
3. If adding a new version, increment suffix: `sif-v4.md`
4. Update `README.md` cross-references when moving or renaming files
5. Update `.cursor/rules/context.md` directory map accordingly
